{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    colored_points = find_non_black_pixels(input_grid)\n    input_grid = add_2x2_grid(point=colored_points[3], color=input_grid[colored_points[0]])\n    input_grid = add_2x2_grid_lower_left(point=colored_points[2], color=input_grid[colored_points[1]])\n    input_grid = add_2x2_grid_upper_right(point=colored_points[2], color=input_grid[colored_points[2]])\n    input_grid = add_2x2_grid_upper_left(point=colored_points[1], color=input_grid[colored_points[3]])\n    return input_grid\ndef add_2x2_grid(point: Tuple[int, int], color: int, input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a point, color, and input grid and adds a 2x2 grid at the lower-right of the color at the point.\n    \n    Args:\n    point: A tuple representing the point where the 2x2 grid needs to be added.\n    color: An integer representing the color of the point.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    input_grid[point[0] + 1][point[1] + 1] = color\n    input_grid[point[0] + 1][point[1] + 2] = color\n    input_grid[point[0] + 2][point[1] + 1] = color\n    input_grid[point[0] + 2][point[1] + 2] = color\n    return input_grid\ndef add_2x2_grid_upper_left(point: Tuple[int, int], color: int, input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a point, color, and input grid and adds a 2x2 grid at the upper-left of the color at the point.\n    \n    Args:\n    point: A tuple representing the point where the 2x2 grid needs to be added.\n    color: An integer representing the color of the point.\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the updated grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    input_grid[point[0] - 1][point[1] - 1] = color\n    input_grid[point[0] - 1][point[1]] = color\n    input_grid[point[0]][point[1] - 1] = c